534
00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:45.937
Our first one is, 
"Is a mega menu accessibility suited 

535
00:36:45.937 --> 00:36:48.400
or can it be made usable?

536
00:36:48.400 --> 00:36:50.909
If so can you describe or provide a sample?" 

537
00:36:50.909 --> 00:36:55.078
Is a mega menu accessible or 
can it be made accessible? 

538
00:36:55.078 --> 00:36:59.287
<v Adam> I guess that would 
entirely depend upon 

539
00:36:59.287 --> 00:37:03.320
whether or not it conforms to WCAG standards. 

540
00:37:03.320 --> 00:37:08.640
Can you navigate the menu using 
a mouse and/or a keyboard?

541
00:37:09.440 --> 00:37:15.380
Does it respond appropriately to a screen reader, 
when you do so? 

542
00:37:15.380 --> 00:37:21.840
For instance my reference point for screen readers 
is the Mac OS screen reader.

543
00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:25.840
Honestly, I don't have 
JAWS or anything like that

544
00:37:27.120 --> 00:37:31.791
and we don't really have to have 
that kind of material where I work. 

545
00:37:31.791 --> 00:37:35.717
But I try to use the 
Mac OS screen reader as best I can. 

546
00:37:35.717 --> 00:37:40.738
I would say that you should just be very careful 

547
00:37:40.738 --> 00:37:43.607
in the case of a mega menu, 

548
00:37:43.607 --> 00:37:47.542
because you may inadvertently hide content

549
00:37:47.542 --> 00:37:51.571
that you would rather have people get to. 

550
00:37:51.571 --> 00:37:55.998
I think that what you should do 
in the case of a mega menu, 

551
00:37:55.998 --> 00:38:01.411
is try to navigate the site 
with the screen reader and see what happens. 

552
00:38:01.411 --> 00:38:04.599
Can you actually get to any of the items? 

553
00:38:04.599 --> 00:38:08.944
Can you get to the items if you only navigate by keyboard? 

554
00:38:08.944 --> 00:38:14.320
I think that will be the determinant 
if it's accessible or not,

555
00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:18.320
better than me just giving a broad, 
yes they are, no they're not.

556
00:38:18.320 --> 00:38:24.320
