00:38:39.080 --> 00:38:42.720
<v Mike> I think so.

561
00:38:42.720 --> 00:38:47.760
<v Adam> I believe that it reads. 
Last I checked it did.

562
00:38:47.760 --> 00:38:51.468
I mean we don't have anything that 

563
00:38:51.468 --> 00:38:56.023
responds to voice commands in these menus. 

564
00:38:56.023 --> 00:38:59.262
Certainly, I don't have the background to handle that. 

565
00:38:59.262 --> 00:39:02.722
Although if it's something that I need to do, 

566
00:39:02.722 --> 00:39:05.520
I can certainly start looking into it.

567
00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:08.828
But as best I know, and the last time I checked, 

568
00:39:08.828 --> 00:39:10.754
yes, they all read correctly. 

569
00:39:10.754 --> 00:39:15.760
<v Mike> Our last question,
(and if anyone has a last minute question

570
00:39:15.760 --> 00:39:21.170
please put it into the chat now 
and we'll try to get to that) is, 

