00:39:21.170 --> 00:39:25.506
"Menus seemed a web feature that hasn't gone away over time.

572
00:39:25.506 --> 00:39:29.515
With Skip NAV and one-page sites becoming more prevalent, 

573
00:39:29.515 --> 00:39:34.560
do you see them being phased out for simple, 
more accessible experiences?"

574
00:39:34.560 --> 00:39:38.080
<v Adam> Oh that's actually, 
really interesting.

575
00:39:41.680 --> 00:39:43.787
We definitely use Skip NAV. 

576
00:39:43.787 --> 00:39:45.903
I have no information about 

577
00:39:45.903 --> 00:39:48.549
how many people actually use that. 

578
00:39:48.549 --> 00:39:51.280
As far as single page sites go,

579
00:39:51.280 --> 00:39:54.125
I think there's a big difference 
between literally 

580
00:39:54.125 --> 00:39:56.324
a single page which is like a brochure 

581
00:39:56.324 --> 00:39:58.354
and a single page application site, 

582
00:39:58.354 --> 00:40:03.291
which is a more, larger scale or something like that. 

583
00:40:03.291 --> 00:40:09.800
In the latter case, or in the in the former case rather, 
literally single page, 

584
00:40:09.800 --> 00:40:14.880
I'm not quite sure why you would 
necessarily need a navigation.

585
00:40:14.880 --> 00:40:18.096
You might just have some links at the top 

586
00:40:18.096 --> 00:40:20.240
that would jump you up and down.

587
00:40:21.280 --> 00:40:24.093
In the latter case, I'm not sure. 

588
00:40:24.093 --> 00:40:28.560
I think that some applications in site are so complex

589
00:40:30.800 --> 00:40:33.385
that you wouldn't necessarily need them. 

590
00:40:33.385 --> 00:40:36.160
I think the only thing that I would say is,

591
00:40:36.160 --> 00:40:40.000
lots of people now get to sites 
just by Googling the information they want.

592
00:40:40.800 --> 00:40:45.008
Then my intuition is that if for some reason

593
00:40:45.008 --> 00:40:48.000
the content doesn't make sense,

594
00:40:48.000 --> 00:40:50.504
or is structured in a bizarre way, 

595
00:40:50.504 --> 00:40:54.097
then they might need to use more navigational elements 

596
00:40:54.097 --> 00:40:58.005
in order to find what they're looking for, after the fact. 

